    "ref_entries": {
        "FIGREF0": {
            "text": "Fig. 1: A) SARS-CoV-2 recognition by Dendritic Cell:\u25aaBinding SARS-CoV-2 to TLR\u25aaActivation of NF\u03baB signaling pathway\u25aaActivation of PI3K/AKT/mTOR signaling pathway\u25aaActivation NLRP3 inflammasome pathway and production of Pro-IL-1\u03b2\u25aaAll these signaling pathways lead to cytokine storm\u25aaRapamycin blocks mTOR and finally inhibits cytokine storm including IL-1\u03b2 and IL-6 B) CD8+ T lymphocytes senescence under cytokine storm and extensive SARS-CoV-2 replication:\u25aaCytokine storm increases the numbers of CD8+ T cells expressing the senescent marker PD-1\u25aaPD-1+ CD8 + T cells become unable to secrete IFN-\u03b3, Perforin, and Granzyme, and to induce apoptosis of SARS-CoV-2 infected cells.",
            "type": "figure"
        }
